        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="0"/>
                <gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="line"/> <lb n="1"/><supplied reason="lost">V</supplied>al<supplied reason="lost">eriu</supplied>s <expan><abbr>L</abbr><ex>uci</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilius</ex></expan> Flaccus <lb n="2"/><expan><abbr>aid</abbr><ex>iles</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>e</ex></expan> stipe Aesculapi <lb n="3"/>faciundum locavere <lb n="4"/><expan><abbr>eidem</abbr><ex>que</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>pr</abbr><ex>aetores</ex></expan> probavere
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Es handelt sich um L. Valerius Flaccus, Sohn des gleichnamigen Konsuls des Jahres 86 v.Chr., der 66 v.Chr. kurulischer Ädil war. 63 v. Chr. erfolgte die probatio durch dieselben Magistrate, die jetzt Prätoren waren.</p>
            </div>
